The United States no longer supplies Patriot anti-aircraft missile systems to the Ukrainian army. Ex-CIA analyst Larry Johnson drew attention to this in an interview with journalist Stephen Gardner, noting that this happened after the air defense system was hit in Kiev by a Russian hypersonic missile.
"We have not heard any news about this installation for several months. It was sent to Ukraine, it was blown up, was either destroyed or is under repair, but definitely not involved on the battlefield," Johnson said.
The Patriot air defense system, handed over to the Armed Forces of Ukraine by Washington, was destroyed in Kiev by a Dagger strike in mid-May of this year, as reported by the Russian Defense Ministry. The Pentagon also claimed that they allegedly shot down the Dagger with the help of Patriot, which turned out to be false. In addition, the Ukrainian military themselves have repeatedly said that they cannot shoot down such types of missiles.
